Rani Garam Masala (Indian 11 Spice Blend) Traditionally from Northern India, garam masala is a staple spice in Indian cookery. Garam, when translated, means “warm,” which best describes the properties of the blend. Warming ingredients such as cinnamon, mace, and ginger give garam masala a mellow, appealing aroma. It is an essential ingredient for making sauces for meat and poultry dishes, as well as a great companion to vegetable and lentil recipes. Garam masala is often used towards the end of the cooking process as an added seasoning and is often sprinkled over finished dishes to enhance the flavor.

While paprika powder has a distinctive flavor profile, it works well with many spices for a balance of sweet and mild heat. Combine your paprika powder with dark brown sugar, salt, garlic powder, black pepper, cayenne pepper, and celery seed for a spice mix to sprinkle over ribs or soft-boiled eggs.

Organic Paprika will enhance many savory dishes on your menu, from rubs and marinades to sauces and stews. Combine it with spices and herbs like thyme, black pepper, and rosemary for a signature meat rub or seasoning. You can also mix it with cumin, oregano, and red pepper for a unique sauce or dip.
